[
    {
        "content": "<p>I wanted to learn Roc compiler and add a fun feature, a syntax sugar for the closure of single argument with pipe,<br>\nwhere this code <code>\\|&gt; foo</code> translates to <code>\\x -&gt; x |&gt; foo</code>.</p>\n<p>From this intent, emerged a general idea of the \"closure shortcut\" for the binary and unary operators, record field and tuple accessors, identity function. The feature is implemented on the level of Parser, and it does not tax other parts of compiler. Underneath the AST is the same, with some small markers for the shortcut nodes. </p>\n<p>The other side of this feature is the Formatter. By default, <code>roc format</code> will keep the shortcut syntax.<br>\nBut you may guide it to expand the shortcut into the full closure form. <br>\nSay you've typed <code>\\|&gt;</code> shortcut, then you can put space between opening <code>\\</code> and <code>|&gt;</code> in <code>\\ |&gt; foo</code> and it will expand into <code>\\x -&gt; x |&gt; foo</code> on format (automatically with format-on-save and auto-save enabled in the editor). </p>\n<p>So it provides editor-like quick snippet functionality in the language itself, which I did not see anywhere else.</p>\n<p>The idea is implemented already as part of <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/pull/7212\">this PR</a> and you can play with it right now :-) More details and examples in the PR description.</p>\n<p>Related ideas: <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"304641\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/Syntax.20sugar.20for.20.22piped.20when.22.3F\">#ideas &gt; Syntax sugar for \"piped when\"?</a>, <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"304641\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/Shorthands.20for.20nested.20records\">#ideas &gt; Shorthands for nested records</a>  </p>\n<p>Examples:</p>\n<p>Binary operators:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Record fields and tuple accessors:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\.</span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[(</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">)]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\.</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">y</span><span class=\"p\">)}}]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\.</span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Identity function:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Unary operators:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\-.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">y</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Combinations:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">y</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\-.</span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Binary operator for the <code>when</code> pattern matching:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">~</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"s\">\"abc\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"abc\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>When operator as closure shortcut:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">\\~</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"s\">\"abc\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"abc\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Combines with the rest:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">\\.</span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">~</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"s\">\"abc\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"abc\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 481602292,
        "sender_full_name": "Maksim Volkau",
        "timestamp": 1731277040
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are these features you hope roc accepts or just exploration?</p>",
        "id": 481604885,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1731279471
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is both. I would love to see my exploration converts to the actual feature.</p>",
        "id": 481605339,
        "sender_full_name": "Maksim Volkau",
        "timestamp": 1731279845
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Isn't <code>\\x -&gt; x |&gt; foo</code> just <code>foo</code>?</p>",
        "id": 481606659,
        "sender_full_name": "Sky Rose",
        "timestamp": 1731281044
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"607308\">Sky Rose</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/Closure.20shortcut.20feature/near/481606659\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Isn't <code>\\x -&gt; x |&gt; foo</code> just <code>foo</code>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>true but if foo has more than one argument then <code>\\x -&gt; x |&gt; foo y</code> isn't the same as <code>foo y</code></p>",
        "id": 481606699,
        "sender_full_name": "Derin Eryilmaz",
        "timestamp": 1731281096
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You may want to break this into a few different proposals. For example the binary when separate from unary dot separate from closure shorthand.</p>",
        "id": 481608276,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1731282399
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I will warn that roc tends to focus on readability in a way that generally does not match this proposal. So it is probably pretty unlikely to be accepted.</p>",
        "id": 481608321,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1731282455
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would like to keep this feature together, as a complete package. <br>\nParts of this feature combine in \"natural\" way  and it is hard to discuss separately. <br>\nAlso, it covers the questions \"what about?\" - If  dot field access supported, what about dot alone? If binary op is supported, what about unary? Etc.</p>",
        "id": 481660601,
        "sender_full_name": "Maksim Volkau",
        "timestamp": 1731313684
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><strong>Update:</strong> I have added Formatter side of the feature into the description, which I forgot last night. Now it should provide the full picture together with the PR.</p>",
        "id": 481762620,
        "sender_full_name": "Maksim Volkau",
        "timestamp": 1731342787
    }
